sections.name: BlockTraits
content: List of all Block Traits and the BlockStates they include.
Experimental toggles required : Upcoming Creator Features

Description: Adds the "minecraft:cardinal_direction" and/or "minecraft:facing_direction" states and setter function to the block. The values of these states are set when the block is placed.

rows.Name: enabled_states
Description: Which states to enable. Must specify at least one.

rows.Name: minecraft:cardinal_direction
rows.Description: Defines the cardinal placement direction of a block.

rows.Name: minecraft:facing_direction
rows.Default Value: down, up, north, south, east, west
rows.Description: Defines all placement directions of a block.

rows.Name: y_rotation_offset
rows.Description: The y rotation offset to apply to the block. Must be [0.0, 90.0, 180.0, 270.0]. Default is 0, meaning if the player is facing north, the "minecraft:cardinal_direction" and/or minecraft:facing_direction state will be north.

Description: Adds the "minecraft:block_face" and/or "minecraft:vertical_half" BlockStates. The value of these state(s) are set when the block is placed.

rows.Name: enabled_states
Description: Which states to enable. Must specify at least one.

rows.Name: minecraft:block_face
rows.Default Value: down, up, north, south, east, west
rows.Description: Which blockface the player placed the block on.

rows.Name: minecraft:vertical_half
rows.Description: Which vertical half of the space the block is placed in.

rows.Name: elements
Description: List of elements that make up the geometry of this block

rows.Name: boxes
Description: List of cubes that make up the geometry of this element

rows.Name: faces
Description: List of the 6 faces of the box. If specified, there MUST be 6 faces (front, back, left side, right side, top, bottom)

rows.Name: material
rows.Description: The material of this face if different from the box's

rows.Name: rotation
rows.Description: UV Rotation of this face. Only acceptable values are 0, 90 and 270 degrees. This allows reusing a texture and just rotating it for different faces

rows.Name: uv
rows.Description: Texture coordinates of this face, given as min x, min y, max x, max y withg values between 0.0 and 1.0

rows.Name: material
rows.Description: The material of this box if different from the element's

rows.Name: origin
rows.Description: The position of the center of the box relative to the geometry

rows.Name: size
rows.Description: Scale of the box in the x, y and z coordinates. A typical block is of scale 1, 1, 1

rows.Name: material
rows.Description: The material of this element if different from the block's

rows.Name: name
rows.Description: Name of the element

rows.Name: parent
rows.Description: Name of the parent element of this element. Pivot and box positions are made relative to the parent element's pivot

rows.Name: pivot
rows.Description: Position in model space of the pivot point of the element. This is used as the "center" position of the element, as well as the point around which to rotate

rows.Name: rotation
rows.Description: The rotation of this element about its pivot

rows.Name: format_version
rows.Description: Version of the block geometry being used. This is used to determine if backwards compatibility is needed

rows.Name: materials
rows.Description: List of materials used by this model

rows.Name: parent
rows.Description: Parent model of this model

rows.Name: skull
rows.Aux Values: 0 = Skeleton1 = Wither2 = Zombie3 = Steve4 = Creeper5 = Dragon6 = Piglin

sections.name: manifest.json
content: The manifest file contains all the basic information about the pack that Minecraft needs to identify it. The tables below contain all the components of the manifest, their individual properties, and what they mean.

rows.Name: capabilities
Description: These are the different features that the pack makes use of that aren't necessarily enabled by default.

rows.Name: chemistry
rows.Description: Allows the pack to add, change or replace Chemistry functionality

rows.Name: editorExtension
rows.Description: Indicates that this pack contains extensions for editing

rows.Name: experimental_custom_ui
rows.Description: Allows HTML files in the pack to be used for custom UI, and scripts in the pack to call and manipulate custom UI

rows.Name: raytraced
rows.Description: Indicates that this pack contains Raytracing Enhanced or Physical Based Materials for rendering

rows.Name: dependencies
Description: This section describes the packs that this pack depends on in order to work. Any packs defined here will be automatically added to the world when this one is added if they are present, or an error will be shown if they aren't. Each entry has the following parameters:

rows.Name: uuid
rows.Description: This is the unique identifier of the pack that this pack depends on. It needs to be the exact same UUID that the pack has defined in the header section of it's manifest file

rows.Name: version
rows.Description: This is the specific version of the pack that your pack depends on. Should match the version the other pack has in its manifest file

rows.Name: format_version
rows.Description: This defines the current version of the manifest. Don't change this unless you have a good reason to

rows.Name: header
Description: This is the heading of the manifest and is required for the manifest to be valid.

rows.Name: allow_random_seed
rows.Description: This option will generate a random seed every time a template is loaded and allow the player to change the seed before creating a new world.

rows.Name: base_game_version
rows.Description: This is the version of the base game your world template requires, specified as [majorVersion, minorVersion, revision].We use this to determine what version of the base game resource and behavior packs to apply when your content is used.

rows.Name: description
rows.Description: This is a short description of the pack. It will appear in the game below the name of the pack. We recommend keeping it to 1-2 lines.

rows.Name: lock_template_options
rows.Description: This option is required for any world templates. This will lock the player from modifying the options of the world.

rows.Name: min_engine_version
rows.Description: This is the minimum version of the game that this pack was written for.  This is a required field for resource and behavior packs. This helps the game identify whether any backwards compatibility is needed for your pack. You should always use the highest version currently available when creating packs

rows.Name: name
rows.Description: This is the name of the pack as it appears within Minecraft. This is a required field.

rows.Name: uuid
rows.Description: This is a special type of identifier that uniquely identifies this pack from any other pack. UUIDs are written in the format xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx where each x is a hexadecimal value (0-9 or a-f). We recommend using an online service to generate this and guarantee their uniqueness (just bing UUID Generator to find some)

rows.Name: version
rows.Description: This is the version of your pack in the format [majorVersion, minorVersion, revision].The version number is used when importing a pack that has been imported before. The new pack will replace the old one if the version is higher, and ignored if it's the same or lower

rows.Name: metadata
Description: This section contains additional data about your pack and is otherwise optional.

rows.Name: authors
rows.Description: Name of the author(s) of the pack

rows.Name: license
rows.Description: The license of the pack

rows.Name: url
rows.Description: The home website of your pack

rows.Name: modules
Description: This section describes the modules that comprise the pack. Each entry here defines one of the kinds of contents of the pack.

rows.Name: description
rows.Description: This is a short description of the module. This is not user-facing at the moment but is a good place to remind yourself why the module is defined

rows.Name: type
rows.Description: This is the type of the module. Can be any of the following: resources, data, client_data, interface, world_template

rows.Name: uuid
rows.Description: This is a unique identifier for the module in the same format as the pack's UUID in the header. This should be different from the pack's UUID, and different for every module

rows.Name: version
rows.Description: This is the version of the module in the same format as the pack's version in the header. This can be used to further identify changes in your pack
